WEBVTT

00:03.200 --> 00:06.000
        Cheers <i>is filmed</i>        
 <i>before a live studio audience.</i> 

00:08.500 --> 00:09.900
    Hi, Dr. Crane.              

00:10.000 --> 00:12.400
FRASIER:                        
Hello, Woody.                   

00:12.400 --> 00:13.600
      Set me up, will you?      

00:13.600 --> 00:14.500
        Coming right up.        

00:14.600 --> 00:15.700
Boy, you know,                  

00:15.700 --> 00:17.100
no matter how many times        
I come in here,                 

00:17.100 --> 00:18.300
I can't get over                
how silly you look              

00:18.300 --> 00:19.400
in that                         
ridiculous outfit.              

00:20.300 --> 00:22.600
            Really?             

00:22.600 --> 00:23.900
    I kind of like it.          

00:23.900 --> 00:25.700
          People treat me with  
          a little more respect.

00:25.800 --> 00:27.300
                  And there's   
                  another bonus.

00:27.300 --> 00:29.100
              Saves me that     
              couple extra hours

00:29.100 --> 00:30.700
                 I used to spend
                 every morning  

00:30.800 --> 00:32.100
            picking out a shirt.

00:33.800 --> 00:36.000
        Yes, that can be        
      very time consuming.      

00:37.400 --> 00:39.200
    Whatever happened           
     to the good old days?      

00:39.200 --> 00:41.500
Everything                      
was better.                     

00:41.500 --> 00:42.800
    Sam still owned the bar.    

00:42.800 --> 00:45.300
         He wasn't out          
  circumnavigating the globe.   

00:45.300 --> 00:47.600
Yonder sat Diane                
with a book.                    

00:47.700 --> 00:50.400
 Norm and Cliff were permanent  
    fixtures in this place.     

00:50.500 --> 00:52.900
        God, how I miss         
  those hail-fellows-well-met.  

00:54.200 --> 00:57.400
Where has it gone, Woody?       

00:57.500 --> 00:59.200
                  Oh, hey, come 
                  on, Dr. Crane.

00:59.300 --> 01:00.700
             It'll be all right.

01:00.700 --> 01:02.300
         ( <i>sniffling</i> ):         
            Will it?            

01:02.300 --> 01:03.500
( <i>blowing nose</i> )                

01:03.500 --> 01:08.600
      "Oh, death in life,       
  the days that are no more."   

01:08.600 --> 01:10.400
         Who said that?         

01:10.500 --> 01:13.600
                  Who said what?

01:13.600 --> 01:16.500
      "Oh, death in life,       
  the days that are no more."   

01:16.600 --> 01:18.300
                    You did.    

01:18.300 --> 01:21.300
        No, no, you see,        
I mean who said it first?       

01:21.400 --> 01:25.100
    Y-You said it both times.   

01:26.900 --> 01:28.500
 You know, you're right, Woody. 

01:28.500 --> 01:30.100
Some things never change.       

01:30.100 --> 01:32.500
  Especially the simple ones.   

01:32.600 --> 01:33.400
        And don't you forget it.

01:33.500 --> 01:34.700
                ( <i>pats counter</i> )

01:36.500 --> 01:40.800
        ( <i>piano plays</i> )         

01:40.800 --> 01:43.100
    ¶ Making your way           
      in the world today ¶      

01:43.200 --> 01:46.200
¶ Takes everything you've got   

01:46.200 --> 01:49.000
        ¶ Taking a break        
    from all your worries ¶     

01:49.000 --> 01:52.400
¶ Sure would help a lot         

01:52.400 --> 01:58.300
      ¶ Wouldn't you like       
         to get away? ¶         

01:58.300 --> 02:00.300
  ¶ Sometimes you want to go    

02:00.300 --> 02:05.800
    ¶ Where everybody           
    knows your name ¶           

02:05.800 --> 02:10.300
¶ And they're always glad       
        you came ¶              

02:10.300 --> 02:12.700
        ¶ You want to be        
      where you can see ¶       

02:12.800 --> 02:15.500
         ¶ Our troubles         
    are all the same ¶          

02:15.500 --> 02:20.700
     ¶ You want to be where     
  everybody knows your name ¶   

02:20.800 --> 02:23.200
        ¶ You want to go        
      where people know ¶       

02:23.300 --> 02:25.900
  ¶ People are all the same     

02:25.900 --> 02:29.900
     ¶ You want to go where     
  everybody knows your name. ¶  

